---
import Site from '../../layouts/Site.astro';
import '../../styles/pages.css';
---

<Site title="Quell Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for Quell, the browser extension by Purple Directive. Quell collects nothing — no analytics, no telemetry, no accounts, no servers.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
    <div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Quell Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Effective date: July 6, 2026 · Last updated: July 14, 2026</p>

    <p>
      Quell is a browser extension by Purple Directive that hides unwanted content
      (AI feature blocks, cookie-consent pop-ups) locally in your browser. This policy
      covers the Quell extension only; the
      <a href="/privacy">Purple Directive website privacy policy</a> covers this website.
    </p>

    <h2>What Quell Collects</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Nothing.</strong> Quell has no analytics, no telemetry, no accounts, and no servers.
    </p>

    <h2>What Quell Stores</h2>
    <p>
      Your settings (which features are on or off, sites where you've paused blocking)
      and a running count of blocked elements are stored in your browser's local
      extension storage (<code>chrome.storage.local</code>) on your device. This data never
      leaves your machine and is deleted when you uninstall the extension.
    </p>

    <h2>What Quell Can Access</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Google and Bing search result pages, to hide AI feature blocks there.</li>
      <li>
        If — and only if — you enable the optional Cookie banners feature, Quell can
        run on the pages you visit to hide consent banners. It reads nothing and
        sends nothing; the access exists solely to inject hiding rules.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Network Activity</h2>
    <p>
      The published extension makes no network requests. Blocklists ship inside the
      extension package and are updated through normal extension updates.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes &amp; Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Material changes to this policy will be reflected in the extension's changelog
      and on this page. Questions:
      <a href="mailto:support@purpledirective.com">support@purpledirective.com</a>.
    </p>
    </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 680px;
    padding: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .legal-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-page h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-page p,
  .legal-page li {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-page ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
  }

  .legal-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--purple-primary);
  }

  .legal-page code {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    background: var(--bg-tinted);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
</style>
